         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">On bord of the ¶  ¶ "Siam" ¶ M was en route from Melbourne to WA. ¶ 5/10/77 ¶  ¶ Allow me, my Lord, to introduce to you the generous supporter of the geographic enterprises of Colonel Warburton and of...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.10.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Lord Arthur Russell</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Geographical Society, London, Archives, RGS correspondence 1871-80, Mueller, Sir Ferdinand.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">On bord of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Siam"<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was en route from Melbourne to WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/10/77</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, my Lord, to introduce to you the generous supporter of the geographic enterprises of Colonel Warburton and of the two last expeditions of Mr Giles.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The hon. Th. Elder is on a visit to his native country, and I feel sure, he will regard it an honor to be introduced to the Royal Geographic Society by your Lordship,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lord Russell was Foreign Secretary of the Royal Geographical Society.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>while the great British forum of geographic research will doubtless recognize the generosity of this excellent man, who rendered known by his private means most extensive tracts of the Australian Continent, and who is likely to promote still further geographic mapping after his return to his Australian Home.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
